  <section>
    <title>Options</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry xml:id="senlin.common.config.list_opts">
        <term>
          <function>senlin.common.config.list_opts</function>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Return a list of oslo.config options available.</para>
          <para>The purpose of this function is to allow tools like the Oslo sample config
                        file generator to discover the options exposed to users by this service.
                        The returned list includes all oslo.config options which may be registered
                        at runtime by the service api/engine.</para>
          <para>Each element of the list is a tuple. The first element is the name of the
                        group under which the list of elements in the second element will be
                        registered. A group name of None corresponds to the [DEFAULT] group in
                        config files.</para>
          <para>This function is also discoverable via the ‘senlin.config’ entry point
                        under the ‘oslo.config.opts’ namespace.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>
